 <H1>Enforcing Referential Integrity</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>Consider Boats and Reserves;  bid in Reserves is a foreign key that references Boats.
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>What should be done if a Reserves tuple with a non-existent boat id is inserted?  (Reject it!)
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>What should be done if a Boats tuple is deleted?
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Also delete all Reserves tuples that refer to it.
<LI>Disallow deletion of a Boats tuple that is referred to.
<LI>Set bid of Reserves tuples that refer to it to a default bid.
<LI>Set bid of Reserves tuples that refer to it to null.
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Same choices if primary key of Boats tuple is updated.</H2>
</UL></P>
